author: The Virginian-Pilot
title: No. 2 Lake Taylor stifles Booker T. Washington
text:
No. 2 Lake Taylor 25, Booker T. Washington 3
The Titans' defense held the Bookers (2-6) to just 62 yards of total offense, all on the ground, as they cruised in an Eastern district match-up.
Dazmine Palmer rushed for 93 yards and scored a pair of touchdowns while quarterback Tyrek Hughey finished with 139 total yards (88 passing, 51 rushing) for Lake Taylor (8-0).
JT Wahee had an interception and a 53-yard kickoff return for a touchdown, and Jaylen Cuffee recovered a fumble in the end zone for a score late in the second quarter to give Lake Taylor a 13-0 lead at the half.
 - Reported by Jamaar Hawkins
